It shouldn't have.
Granted, the place is fu-fu like we expected, but seven guys didn't really want to go and share skinny slices of beef.
The sushi was decent, but not great by any means.
The service was good and the waitress was Japanese (this may not matter to some, but it always adds a little bit to my experience at any Japanese joint).
