This was good and I would definitely get it again.
Being that it was 9 hungry girls, I didn't get to try many other dishes, but the tuna ceviche (more of a tartare in my eyes) looked great, as did some of the robata grill items.
In the interest of saving money I ordered a plain salmon roll...nothing special and nothing big - probably would order off the specialty sushi rolls next time.
All in all it was a good meal, made better by our server.
Yes Japonais is expensive, maybe slightly more expensive than it should be, but it's on the strip, inside a hotel in tourist central and is probably priced just right for what it is.
I have to admit that the ambiance inside is great, and if you sit in the outer lounge area you do get a great view of the robata grill at work.

